Program: Outlook
Title: 27/09/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00k8tsd
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 28 Sep 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, a Japanese woman describes being sucked into a whirlpool when the tsunami overwhelmed her town. Also, two Americans trying to escape the electromagnetic fields which they say are making them ill. And a Kenyan-Somali doctor talks about the challenges he faces in the Dadaab refugee camp. Show less